"This Cartier has undergone a thorough inspection of accuracy, functionality and condition at our Cartier certified service centre to determine the level of reconditioning required to meet our strict standards. It has also been checked against our records to ensure authenticity.", "
                            Invented in 1904, the Santos was the first ever men's wristwatch, originally invented for aviation pioneer Alberto Santos-Dumont to make it easier to check the time while flying. The watch was a game-changer in the industry thanks to Santos-Dumont's huge popularity and fame, and to celebrate the origins of the timepiece, Cartier produced a wonderful series of Santos watches called the Santos 100. Modern Santos watches still maintain the classic hallmarks of the original, including the rounded square case, Roman numeral hour markers and fully incorporated lugs—as well as the wonderful gold bezel on this model. 
                            
                        "

description:
"
                            The Seamaster is one of the most iconic diving watches of all time. Following from Omega's Marine in 1932, the world's first commercially available diving watch, the legend of the Seamaster officially debuted in 1948. By the time of 1957's 300M, it was among the most dependable and professionally sought dive watches from any brand, and it soon pioneered some of the sporty must-have features we associate with such watches, including unidirectional bezels, phosphorescent hands and the helium escape valve. This excellent model is a closely related sister watch to the version made famous by Pierce Brosnan as James Bond in 1995's GoldenEye—kicking off Bond's attachment to the Seamaster that continues to this day.

title: "Garmin Forerunner 15 Large HRM 1- Black/Blue"@en " Garmin Accessories - Black/Blue "@en
description:
"
                                    The Forerunner 15 tracks distance, pace, calories and heart rate (HRM included). The activity tracking counts steps and calories and reminds you when it’s time to move. The watch is also compatible with foot pod (sold separately) for recording distance indoors. The battery life is up to 8 hours with GPS on or 5 weeks in watch/activity tracking mode. Further functions of the watch enable you to save, plan and share your activities at Garmin Connect™.As well as capturing essential stats from your run like time, distance and pace, when paired with a heart rate monitor (included) the Forerunner 15 also records your heart rate and heart rate zone so you’ll know when you hit your target. Training with heart rate also allows you to monitor when you need to rein it in and when you can push yourself harder.The watch also has an auto lap function that automatically alerts you when you complete each mile, giving you a beep and a backlit screen that flashes your time for that mile. When you complete your run and save it, you’ll see a summary of how you did, including your total time, distance, average pace and calories. Forerunner 15 even lets you know when you achieve a personal record, like your fastest mile or longest run to date.For outdoor runs, Forerunner 15 uses GPS to accurately record your time, pace and distance. To track distance and pace when you hit the treadmill or an indoor track, just pair Forerunner 15 with an optional foot pod, which attaches to the laces of your shoe.Forerunner 15 counts your steps and the calories you burn all day. When you upload your data to Garmin Connect, this allows you to monitor your progress toward fitness goals and see overall fitness trends. Forerunner 15 also reminds you when it’s time to move if you’ve been sitting for more than an hour. When you get that cue to move, just walk for a couple of minutes to reset the inactivity indicator.You won’t have to worry about charging Forerunner every night. The rechargeable battery will last up to 5 weeks in watch/activity tracking mode or 8 hours when using it with GPS on your outdoor runs. Forerunner 15 has a water rating of 5 ATM (50 meters), which means it resists rain and sweat and can even join you for a swim.With a simple connection to your Mac® or PC, you can upload your activities to Garmin’s free online fitness community, Garmin Connect. Here, you can see your run on a map, get more detail on each mile, see a daily summary of your activities and share with friends. You can also join online challenges and earn virtual badges for extra motivation.Physical dimensions - 1.79” x 2.25” x 0.62” (45.5 x 57.2 x 15.7 mm)Display size, WxH - 0.98” x 0.94” (25 x 24 mm)Display resolution, WxH - 52 x 32 pixelsWeight - Large: 43 g (1.5 oz)Features Include:- Tracks distance pace calories and heart rate- Heart Rate Monitor/strap (HRM) included- Activity tracking counts steps and calories and reminds you when it’s time to move- Compatible with foot pod for recording distance indoors- Up to 8 hours of battery life with GPS on or 5 weeks in watch/activity tracking mode- Save plan and share your activities at Garmin Connect™- Virtual Pacer™ (compares current pace to target)- Personal records- Auto Pause® (pauses and resumes timer based on speed)- Auto Lap® (automatically starts a new lap)- Heart rate-based calorie computation- Calculates calories burned- Customizable screen(s)- Shock Resistant- Step counter- Auto goal (learns your activity level and assigns a daily step goal)- Move bar (displays on device after a period of inactivity; walk for a couple of minutes to reset it)- Sleep monitoring (monitors total sleep and periods of movement or restful sleep)IN THE BOX YOU WILL FIND:- Forerunner 15- Heart rate monitor- Charging/data cable- Manual

title: " Junghans Men's Meister Pilot Automatic Chronograph Watch"@en "Men's Watch (027/3591.00) - WATCH SHOP.com™"@en
description:
"The high demands placed on timekeeping by aviation were first addressed by Junghans in the 1930s, when the company produced on-board clocks for air traffic use.

These were manufactured in level 7 of the now heritage-listed terrace building, the structure offered optimal lighting conditions for the delicate task of watchmaking. The classic instrument appearance of the cockpit was also reflected in the legendary Bundeswehr chronograph of 1955. The design of the Meister Pilot harks back to this: on the bi-directional rotating bezel the 12 distinctive, concave notches ensure a good grip as well as the unmistakable appearance of the timepiece. The screwed case back features a distinctive element: a specially-designed compass rose, which incorporates the symbolism of classic aviation in the form of an artificial horizon. The riveted leather strap ensures a secure fit on the wrist. The particular construction of the front assembly lends the timepiece an unusual elegance for a pilot watch – and the lightness required for take-off."@en

					Artikel-Nr.: 1930 SKW6237
					
					Modisch-elegante Herrenuhr der Marke Skagen.
					

					Das Gehäuse ist aus hochwertigen, massiven Edelstahl hergestellt und hat eine polierte Oberfläche.
					

					Auf dem blauen Zifferblatt befindet sich ein Skagen Schriftzug.
					

					Die Zeiger und IndizesIndizes ist das deutsche Wort für das lateinische Index. Spricht man von Indizes, dann sind die Zahlen die die Zeit anzeigen (bei vielen Uhren z.B. arabische Zahlen: 3, 6, 9, 12, aber auch z.B. römische Zahlen: III, VI, IX, XII) oder stattdessen die Platzhalter dafür gemeint. Platzhalter können je nach Gestaltung der Uhr die Unterschiedlichsten Formen haben. Uhrenindexe werden oft nicht nur aufgemalt sondern auch aufgesetzt – bei exklusiven Uhren auch veredelt (mit z.B. Gold, Rosegold, Silber, Chrom). Noch Fragen? Hier geht es zum Uhren-Lexikon sind mit einer Leuchtmasse gefüllt, damit auch im Dunkeln die Uhrzeit gut lesbar ist.
					

					Auf dem Zifferblattrand befindet sich eine vollständige MinuterieAuf dem Zifferblatt umlaufende Einteilung der Minuten, oft zwischen zwei Kreise eingefaßt (‘Eisenbahnminuterie = sieht aus wie Eisenbahnschienen) und teilweise mit ‘5’-Minutenzahlen versehen. Noch Fragen? Hier geht es zum Uhren-Lexikon.
					

					Ein Mineralglas schützt das Zifferblatt optimal vor äußeren Einflüssen.
					

					Das Gehäuse hat einen Durchmesser von ca. 40 mm und eine Höhe von ca. 6 mm.
					

					Das Band ist aus braunem Leder gefertigt und verspricht einen angenehmen Tragekomfort.
					

					Verschlossen wird das Lederband mit einer DornschließeEine Dornschließe beschreibt die Verschlussart einer Uhr.  In dem längeren Armbandteil werden löcher gestanzt. Auf der anderen Seite befindet sich die Dornschließe, welche aus einem Dorn und einem Metallbügel in U-Form, diese verhindert, dass der Dorn aus dem Loch rutscht.
Dornschließen sind an diversen Materialien zu finden und erstrecken sich in alle Preisklasse. Häufig findet man Dornschließen bei Lederarmbändern oder Textilarmbändern.

 Noch Fragen? Hier geht es zum Uhren-Lexikon.

					Artikel-Nr.: 4216 GW-9400-1ER
					
					Sportliche Digitaluhr für Herren der Marke Casio.
					

					Das Logo ist befindet sich auf dem schwarzen Gehäuse.
					

					Die Uhr macht einiges mit, ohne Schaden zu nehmen. Die Stoßfestigkeit bietet Schutz bei Aufprall und Erschütterungen.
					

					Für das Super Full Auto LED Light genügt eine leichte Drehung des Handgelenks, um den Hintergrund der Uhr besonders hell in einer modischen Farbe zu beleuchten.
					

					Unabhängig und umweltfreundlich sorgen Solarzellen für die Energieversorgung der Uhr. Überschüssige Solarenergie wird in einem Akku gespeichert.
					

					Ein spezieller Sensor misst den Luftdruck (Messbereich: 260/1.100 hPa.) und zeigt diesen symbolisch auf dem Display an. Damit ist es möglich, vorzeitig Wettertendenzen zu erkennen.
					

					Ein Sensor misst die Umgebungstemperatur der Uhr und zeigt diese in Grad CelsiusGrad Celsius ist eine Maßeinheit der Temperatur. Noch Fragen? Hier geht es zum Uhren-Lexikon (-10°C /+60°C) an.
					

					Ein Richtungssensor stellt die magnetische Nord-Richtung fest und zeigt diese digital an.
					

					Ein Drucksensor stellt Änderungen im Luftdruck fest und rechnet das Ergebnis in Höhenangaben bis 10.000 m um.
					

					Nach Eingabe der geografischen Lage können die Sonnenauf- und -untergangszeiten für jedes beliebige Datum angezeigt werden.
					

					Die Weltzeit Funktion zeigt die Uhrzeiten in bis zu 29 verschiedenen ZeitzonenEs gibt insgesamt 24 Zeitzonen, die je 15 Längengrade umfassen und beim Nullmeridian beginnen. Beim Übergang von einer zur folgenden Zeitzone verschiebt sich die Zeit um eine Stunde. Je nach Himmelsrichtung verschiebt sich die Zeit entweder eine Stunde nach hinten ( Westen) oder nach vorne (Osten).
Die wichtigsten internationalen Zeitsignale sind: DCF77 (Deutschland) in Mainflingen in Hessen, MSF (Großbritannien) in Anthorn, JJY (Japan), WWV (USA) in Fort Collins, WWVH (USA) auf Hawaii, BPC (China) in Shangqiu

 Noch Fragen? Hier geht es zum Uhren-Lexikon an.
					

					Der Countdown-Timer hilft bei der Erinnerung an besondere oder wiederkehrende Ereignisse, indem er zum eingestellten Zeitpunkt ein akustisches Signal abgibt.
					

					An täglich wiederkehrende Ereignisse erinnert der Tagesalarm, bei dem ein akustisches Signal zum eingestellten Zeitpunkt ertönt. Zusätzlich macht ein abstellbarer Alarm auf den Ablauf jeder vollen Stunde aufmerksam.
					

					Auf Wunsch können die Tastentöne mit der Modetaste abgeschaltet werden. Nach dem Abschalten gibt es dann keinen Piepton mehr, wenn von einer Funktion in die nächste gewechselt wird.
					

					Einmal eingestellt zeigt der automatische Kalender immer das richtige Datum an.
					

					Die Zeitanzeige ist wahlweise einstellbar auf 12- oder 24-Stunden-Format.
					

					Das harte, kratzfeste Mineralglas schützt die Uhr vor Beschädigungen.
					

					Die Uhr ist wasserdicht bis 20 Bar / 200 Meter. Die Meter Angabe bezieht sich nicht auf eine Tauchtiefe, sondern auf den Luftdruck, welcher im Rahmen der WasserdichtigkeitsprDie Angaben über die  Wasserdichtigkeit von Uhren führen immer wieder zu Missverständnissen, da die  angegebenen Meterangaben meist wenig Aussagekraft haben. Im Folgenden nun ein  paar Richtlinien, die den richtigen Umgang mit ihrer Uhr und Wasser erleichtern  sollen:
Es kann auch vorkommen, dass die Angabe der Wasserdichtigkeit in Bar statt Metern vorliegt. Dies ist  dann folgendermaßen zu verstehen:
3 bar = 30 m / 5 bar = 50 m  / 10 bar = 100 m / 20 bar = 200 m 	 Noch Fragen? Hier geht es zum Uhren-Lexikonüfung angewendet wurde. (ISO 22810)

title: "Casio G-Shock GA-100-1A2"@en GA-100-1A2 - Casio Watches"@en
description:
"Casio G-Shock GA-100-1A2ER: shock-resistant, magnetic-resistant, countdown timer, stopwatch, daily alarm, 200-meter water resistance.

Auto-LED light
A light-emitting diode (LED) is used to illuminate the watch face, incl. the feature of an Auto Light Switch that illuminates the display when the watch is angled towards the face.

Shock-resistant
Shock-resistant construction protects against impact and vibration.

Magnetic-resistant
The housing is designed to shield the clock from magnetic fields.

World time function
Displays the current time in major cities and specific areas around the world.

Stopwatch function - 1/1000 sec. - 100 hours
Elapsed time, split time and final time are measured with 1/1000-sec accuracy. The watch can measure times of up to 100 hours.

Timer - 1/1 min. - 24 hours (with automatic repeat)
For fans of precision: the countdown timers help you to remember specific or recurring events by giving off an audible signal at a preset time. They then count back automatically from the preset time. The time can be set to the nearest minute and up to 24 hours in advance. Ideal for people who need to take medicines every day or those who do interval training.

5 daily alarms
The daily alarm reminds you about recurring events with an acoustic signal at the time you have set. This model has 5 independent alarms for flexible reminders of important appointments.

Snooze feature
Each time you stop the alarm, it sounds again after a few minutes.

Speed display
The average speed for a travelled route can be measured. Simply enter the distance at the start and press the stop watch when the destination has been reached - and the average speed is shown.

Automatic calendar
Once set, the automatic calendar always displays the correct date.

12/24-hour timekeeping
Times can be displayed in either a 12-hour or 24-hour format.

Mineral glass
The tough mineral glass resists scratching.

Resin band
Synthetic resin is the ideal material for wrist straps thanks to its extremely durable and flexible properties

2 Years - 1 Battery
The battery supplies the watch with sufficient energy for approx. two years.

Water resistance classification (20 bar)
Perfect for free diving without scuba gear: the watch is water resistant up to 20 bar according to ISO 22810.

Chronometric precision
+/- 15 Seconds per month

Dimensions
55,0 mm x 51,2 mm x 16,9 mm (H x W x D)

Weight
72,0 g

                            The Cartier Tank has been a design milestone since its inception in the early 20th century. Unlike the modified pocket watches being made by other manufacturers, the Tank used a new case design—inspired by the shape of a tank—that actually incorporated the lugs into its shape, rather than adding them as an afterthought. Other iconic design elements include the blued sword hands, Roman numerals, elegant square dial and octagonal crown complete with sapphire cabochon. The Française collection adds a somewhat sportier, more modern feel to an already superb timepiece, making it bolder and more versatile, in large part thanks to its chain-link bracelet.
                            
                        "

title: "Rolex GMT Master II 116713 LN" LN Watch | Watchfinder & Co."
description:
"This Rolex has undergone a thorough inspection of water resistance, accuracy, functionality and condition to determine the level of reconditioning required to meet our strict standards. It has also been referenced against technical documents and manufacturer records where available to ensure authenticity and a clean history.", "
                            The GMT Master was first commissioned in the 1950s by pioneering airline Pan Am, and was designed for aviation. An increase in flight distances created demand for a watch that was able to tell the time in two different parts of the world simultaneously, so Rolex built it with an additional hand that could be set to a second time zone. By the 1980s, the watch had developed into the GMT Master II and was already a favourite among collectors. This model represents a significant upgrade for the watch, boasting an aerospace-grade steel case and cerachrom inserts in the bezel. A variant on the regular 116710, this reference features gold elements in the bezel, crown, hands, indices and of course the bracelet.
                            
                        "

"Rolex GMT Master II 116713 LN" LN Watch | Watchfinder & Co."
description:
"This Rolex has undergone a thorough inspection of water resistance, accuracy, functionality and condition to determine the level of reconditioning required to meet our strict standards. It has also been referenced against technical documents and manufacturer records where available to ensure authenticity and a clean history.", "
                            The GMT Master was first commissioned in the 1950s by pioneering airline Pan Am, and was designed for aviation. An increase in flight distances created demand for a watch that was able to tell the time in two different parts of the world simultaneously, so Rolex built it with an additional hand that could be set to a second time zone. By the 1980s, the watch had developed into the GMT Master II and was already a favourite among collectors. This model represents a significant upgrade for the watch, boasting an aerospace-grade steel case and cerachrom inserts in the bezel. description:
"
                            It was in 1904 that Louis Cartier gave a watch to his good friend and aviation pioneer Alberto Santos-Dumont that was designed to be worn on the wrist. The Santos watch was the first ever men's wristwatch, originally invented to make it easier to check the time while flying. It was a game-changer in the industry thanks to Santos-Dumont's huge popularity and fame, as well as a very early example of the iconic Art Deco style that would influence fashion and watchmaking for decades. The modern Santos watches maintain the classic hallmarks of the original, including the rounded square case, Roman numerals and fully incorporated lugs.

title: "Rolex Milgauss 116400 GV" GV Watch | Watchfinder & Co."
description:
"This Rolex has undergone a thorough inspection of water resistance, accuracy, functionality and condition to determine the level of reconditioning required to meet our strict standards. It has also been referenced against technical documents and manufacturer records where available to ensure authenticity and a clean history.", "
                            Like many of its iconic watch families, Rolex's Milgauss was created in 1956 with a specific market in mind: scientists, power station workers and anyone else exposed to high magnetic fields. It was designed to be able to resist fields up to 1,000 gauss (hence the name—“mille” is Latin for thousand). The watch built a solid reputation with only two models until 1988, and was happily revived two decades later in a modern re-edition that remains faithful to the original purpose and aesthetics—including the beloved lightning bolt hand. This gorgeous GV version (Glace Verte) has a green-tinted dial crystal, and uses a Parachrom-Blu hairspring for even better magnetic and shock resistance.
                            
                        "

Customise Your Watch and Your TrainingNo two runners are the same, and neither are their goals. Set yourself up to reach yours by downloading advanced workouts and training plans to your watch from Garmin Connect. You can even customise your data fields, and download watch faces, widgets and applications all for free at Connect IQ.
On and Off the Road RunningA built-in accelerometer captures distance and pace data when you´re running on an indoor track or treadmill, with no need for a separate foot pod accessory. Once you´re done running, it doubles as an activity tracker, counting your steps and calories throughout the day. It also reminds you to move after sitting for more than an hour. Forerunner 230 is compatible with GPS and GLONASS satellites to locate your position quickly and precisely whether you´re running deep in the woods or near tall buildings. Colourful graphic interface shows your heart rate zone and beats per minute at a glance.
Get ConnectedWhen you download the free Garmin Connect Mobile app to your smartphone, Forerunner 230 offers automatic uploads to our online community where you can save, plan and share your activities. You can also view your data on a desktop by plugging in your device and opening Garmin Connect on a web browser. Additional connected features include live tracking, which allows your friends and fans to follow along and see your stats in real time. If you run with your smartphone, audio prompts will keep you on pace with lap and lap time reminders.

title: "Omega Seamaster 300m 2254.50.00" 2254.50.00 Watch | Watchfinder & Co."
description:
"
                            The Seamaster is one of the most iconic diving watches of all time. Following on from Omega's Marine in 1932, the world's first commercially available diving watch, the legend of the Seamaster officially debuted in 1948. By the time of 1957's 300M, it was among the most dependable and professionally sought dive watches from any brand, and it soon pioneered some of the sporty must-have features we associate with such watches, including unidirectional bezels, phosphorescent hands and the helium escape valve. This excellent example takes the familiar technical specs and design cues from the early Seamasters and updates them with modern aesthetics.

Together with Polar Smart Coaching you can assess your day-to-day fitness levels, plan your individual training, work out at the right intensity and receive instant feedback - designed for maximum enjoyment and motivation.Track everything you need to know about your day, starting with monitoring your sleep quality and going on to your steps, distance, calories burned and any activity you do. The rest of the time you can also stay on top of texts, appointments, and social media by getting alerts directly on your wrist.The great thing about the Polar A360, is that it now comes with the ability to measure your speed and distance based on the movement of your wrist - indoors and out, as long as you use any of the running or basic walking sport profiles - without the need for GPS. To take advantage of this, simply update your Polar A360 to software version 1.2.25 and make sure to specify your handedness and other physical settings for accurate readings. description:
"

Suunto sports watch Alpha Traverse Stealth GPS/Glonass functionality. Outdoor activities will always be under control with this new versatile and reliable measurement and navigation tool. The Alpha version is designed for outdoor works related to hunting and fishing.

Go Explore
Suunto Traverse Alpha conjugates qualities of a sturdy structure and a full range of features for outdoors. Is your guide in the wilderness, which helps keep the GPS/GLONASS navigation guidance. Specific features for hunting and fishing will provide useful tools for your business, including the timing of lunar phases, stroke detection, the alert dawn, the weather trend indicator, and the red backlight for night use. Plan routes and keep a diary of your fishing and hunting outings with SuunTo Movescount.com.

The moon phase calendar based on the position with the time of rise and decline of the Moon helps you determine the best times for fishing, while the barometric pressure graph allows you to precisely follow the weather changes.

Automatic identification of hit tracks the number and position of the strokes. While exploring, you can use the specific POI to mark the routes and important positions. Sunrise and sunset Alerts help you plan your day, while customizable red backlight does not interfere with your night vision.

Create routes on Suunto Movescount with topographic maps and elevation data. View profile of altitude of your itinerary directly from the watch. The atmospheric pressure measurement integrated sensor keeps track of your climb with precision. Save points of interest along the route and,If necessary, retrace your steps with the automatic route tracking feature (breadcrumb). Using the digital compass to orient yourself quickly on unknown territory.

With knurled stainless steel bezel, black nylon strap waterproof and scratch-resistant Sapphire Crystal, Suunto Traverse Alpha is the perfect watch for hunters, fishermen and hikers who want an extremely durable. Vibrating alerts and the red backlight, compatible with night vision goggles, they make you go unnoticed.

Outdoor watches, Suunto sleepers and Traverse Alpha have been tested in accordance with military standards (MIL STD 819G). Have passed the 19 tests, including tests for vibration, shock, drop, freezing and thawing, rain, humidity, immersion, dust and sand.

Dominates the area with GPS/GLONASS navigation: uses features specific to the cacCIA, fishing and hiking. Suunto Traverse is manufactured in Finland and tested according to military standards.

Main features:
-How hiking, fishing and hunting
-Hours and warnings of sunrise and sunset
-POI types specific to fishing and hunting
-Moon phases and times of rise and decline of the Moon
-Automatic detection of stroke
-Red Backlight, night vision compatible

-Automatic route tracking feature (breadcrumb) in real time
-Detection of speed, distance and altitude
-Route planning in Suunto Movescount.com with topographic maps

Weather trends and storm alarm
-Knockthe
-Backlight flashlight mode

-GPS update now
-Monitoring of steps and calories during daily activities, weekly, monthly, and yearly
-Notifications on your phone
-Compatible with Suunto Movescount (iOS and Android)

Package contents:

-Quick Start Guide

title: "Rolex GMT Master II 116713 LN" LN Watch | Watchfinder & Co."
description:
"This Rolex has undergone a thorough inspection of water resistance, accuracy, functionality and condition to determine the level of reconditioning required to meet our strict standards. It has also been referenced against technical documents and manufacturer records where available to ensure authenticity and a clean history.", "
                            The GMT Master was first commissioned in the 1950s by pioneering airline Pan Am, and was designed for aviation. An increase in flight distances created demand for a watch that was able to tell the time in two different parts of the world simultaneously, so Rolex built it with an additional hand that could be set to a second time zone. By the 1980s, the watch had developed into the GMT Master II and was already a favourite among collectors. This model represents a significant upgrade for the watch, boasting an aerospace-grade steel case and cerachrom inserts in the bezel. A variant on the regular 116710, this reference features gold elements in the bezel, crown, hands, indices and of course the bracelet.
                            
                        "

title: " Junghans Men's Meister Pilot Automatic Chronograph Watch"@en "Men's Watch (027/3591.00) - WATCH SHOP.com™"@en
description:
"The high demands placed on timekeeping by aviation were first addressed by Junghans in the 1930s, when the company produced on-board clocks for air traffic use.

These were manufactured in level 7 of the now heritage-listed terrace building, the structure offered optimal lighting conditions for the delicate task of watchmaking. The classic instrument appearance of the cockpit was also reflected in the legendary Bundeswehr chronograph of 1955. The design of the Meister Pilot harks back to this: on the bi-directional rotating bezel the 12 distinctive, concave notches ensure a good grip as well as the unmistakable appearance of the timepiece. The screwed case back features a distinctive element: a specially-designed compass rose, which incorporates the symbolism of classic aviation in the form of an artificial horizon. The riveted leather strap ensures a secure fit on the wrist. The particular construction of the front assembly lends the timepiece an unusual elegance for a pilot watch – and the lightness required for take-off."@en

title: "Rolex GMT Master II 116713 LN" LN Watch | Watchfinder & Co."
description:
"This Rolex has undergone a thorough inspection of water resistance, accuracy, functionality and condition to determine the level of reconditioning required to meet our strict standards. It has also been referenced against technical documents and manufacturer records where available to ensure authenticity and a clean history.", "
                            The GMT Master was first commissioned in the 1950s by pioneering airline Pan Am, and was designed for aviation. An increase in flight distances created demand for a watch that was able to tell the time in two different parts of the world simultaneously, so Rolex built it with an additional hand that could be set to a second time zone. By the 1980s, the watch had developed into the GMT Master II and was already a favourite among collectors. This model represents a significant upgrade for the watch, boasting an aerospace-grade steel case and cerachrom inserts in the bezel. A variant on the regular 116710, this reference features gold elements in the bezel, crown, hands, indices and of course the bracelet.
                            
                        "

description:
"Casio Wave Ceptor WV-58DE-1AVEF: radio controlled, countdown timer, stopwatch, daily alarm, 5 bar water resistance.

 

Illuminator
At the touch of a button, the display can be brightly illuminated.

Radio signal reception (EU, USA, Japan, China)
Whether in Europe, North America and Japan or in the outer reaches of Canada, Central America and China - once the watch has been set to the local time, it receives the relevant signal and shows the correct time wherever you are. In many countries, it also sets itself automatically to summer and winter time.

World time function
Displays the current time in major cities and specific areas around the world.

Stopwatch function - 1/100 sec. - 1 hour
Elapsed time, split time and final time are measured with 1/100-sec accuracy. The watch can measure times of up to 1 hour.

Timer - 1/1 min. - 1 hour
For fans of precision: the countdown timers help you to remember specific or recurring events by giving off an audible signal at a preset time. The time can be set to the nearest minute and up to 1 hour in advance.

Alarm Function    

Daily Alarm: sounds each day at the time you set

Button tones on/off
The button tones for using the mode button can be turned off. This means that the watch no longer beeps when switching from one function to another. Preset alarm or countdown timers remain active when the button tones are deactivated.

12/24-hour timekeeping
Times can be displayed in either a 12-hour or 24-hour format.

Stainless steel band
Tough, durable and elegant: The stainless steel wrist strap gives your watch that classic feel.

Safety Catch
Always reliable: This watch has a particularly secure safety catch, which helps prevent the strap from opening by mistake.

Daily Alarm: sounds each day at the time you set

2 Years - 1 Battery
The battery supplies the watch with sufficient energy for approx. two years.

Water resistance classification (5 bar)
Suitable for swimming, white water rafting, non-snorkeling water related work, and fishing.

Weight

description:
"Casio Wave Ceptor WV-58DE-1AVEF: radio controlled, countdown timer, stopwatch, daily alarm, 5 bar water resistance.

 

Illuminator
At the touch of a button, the display can be brightly illuminated.

Radio signal reception (EU, USA, Japan, China)
Whether in Europe, North America and Japan or in the outer reaches of Canada, Central America and China - once the watch has been set to the local time, it receives the relevant signal and shows the correct time wherever you are. In many countries, it also sets itself automatically to summer and winter time.

World time function
Displays the current time in major cities and specific areas around the world.

Stopwatch function - 1/100 sec. - 1 hour
Elapsed time, split time and final time are measured with 1/100-sec accuracy. The watch can measure times of up to 1 hour.

Timer - 1/1 min. - 1 hour
For fans of precision: the countdown timers help you to remember specific or recurring events by giving off an audible signal at a preset time. The time can be set to the nearest minute and up to 1 hour in advance.

Alarm Function    

Daily Alarm: sounds each day at the time you set

Button tones on/off
The button tones for using the mode button can be turned off. This means that the watch no longer beeps when switching from one function to another. Preset alarm or countdown timers remain active when the button tones are deactivated.

12/24-hour timekeeping
Times can be displayed in either a 12-hour or 24-hour format.

Stainless steel band
Tough, durable and elegant: The stainless steel wrist strap gives your watch that classic feel.

Safety Catch
Always reliable: This watch has a particularly secure safety catch, which helps prevent the strap from opening by mistake.

Daily Alarm: sounds each day at the time you set

2 Years - 1 Battery
The battery supplies the watch with sufficient energy for approx. two years.

Water resistance classification (5 bar)
Suitable for swimming, white water rafting, non-snorkeling water related work, and fishing.

Dimensions
53,4 mm x 43,7 mm x 12,0 mm (H x W x D)

Weight
43,0 g

                            The Cartier Tank has been a design milestone since its inception in the early 20th century. Unlike the modified pocket watches being made by other manufacturers, the Tank used a new case design—inspired by the shape of a tank—that actually incorporated the lugs into its shape, rather than adding them as an afterthought. Other iconic design elements include the blued sword hands, Roman numerals, elegant square dial and octagonal crown complete with sapphire cabochon. The Française collection adds a somewhat sportier, more modern feel to an already superb timepiece, making it bolder and more versatile, in large part thanks to its chain-link bracelet.
                            
                        "

title: " Junghans Men's Meister Pilot Automatic Chronograph Watch"@en "Men's Watch (027/3591.00) - WATCH SHOP.com™"@en
description:
"The high demands placed on timekeeping by aviation were first addressed by Junghans in the 1930s, when the company produced on-board clocks for air traffic use.

These were manufactured in level 7 of the now heritage-listed terrace building, the structure offered optimal lighting conditions for the delicate task of watchmaking. The classic instrument appearance of the cockpit was also reflected in the legendary Bundeswehr chronograph of 1955. The design of the Meister Pilot harks back to this: on the bi-directional rotating bezel the 12 distinctive, concave notches ensure a good grip as well as the unmistakable appearance of the timepiece. The screwed case back features a distinctive element: a specially-designed compass rose, which incorporates the symbolism of classic aviation in the form of an artificial horizon. The riveted leather strap ensures a secure fit on the wrist. The particular construction of the front assembly lends the timepiece an unusual elegance for a pilot watch – and the lightness required for take-off."@en

description:

                            Invented in 1904, the Santos was the first ever men's wristwatch, originally invented for aviation pioneer Alberto Santos-Dumont to make it easier to check the time while flying. The watch was a game-changer in the industry thanks to Santos-Dumont's huge popularity and fame, and to celebrate the origins of the timepiece, Cartier produced a wonderful series of Santos watches called the Santos 100. Modern Santos watches still maintain the classic hallmarks of the original, including the rounded square case, Roman numeral hour markers and fully incorporated lugs—as well as the wonderful gold bezel on this model. 
                            
                        "

					Die Oberfläche ist poliert und hat eine silberne IP Beschichtung.
					

					Gehäuse, Zeiger und IndizesIndizes ist das deutsche Wort für das lateinische Index. Spricht man von Indizes, dann sind die Zahlen die die Zeit anzeigen (bei vielen Uhren z.B. arabische Zahlen: 3, 6, 9, 12, aber auch z.B. römische Zahlen: III, VI, IX, XII) oder stattdessen die Platzhalter dafür gemeint. Platzhalter können je nach Gestaltung der Uhr die Unterschiedlichsten Formen haben. Uhrenindexe werden oft nicht nur aufgemalt sondern auch aufgesetzt – bei exklusiven Uhren auch veredelt (mit z.B. Gold, Rosegold, Silber, Chrom). Noch Fragen? Hier geht es zum Uhren-Lexikon sind aus hochwertigen Edelstahl hergestellt und silbern beschichtet.
					

					Auf dem Zifferblatt befindet sich ein Daniel Wellington Schriftzug mit Logo.
					

					Das Mineralglas schützt die Uhr vor äußeren Einflüssen.
					

					Der Gehäusedurchmesser beträgt ca. 36 mm und hat eine Höhe von ca. 6 mm.
					

					Das hochwertige Lederarmband gewährt einen angenehmen Tragekomfort.
					

					Das Band wird mit einer DornschließeEine Dornschließe beschreibt die Verschlussart einer Uhr.  In dem längeren Armbandteil werden löcher gestanzt. Auf der anderen Seite befindet sich die Dornschließe, welche aus einem Dorn und einem Metallbügel in U-Form, diese verhindert, dass der Dorn aus dem Loch rutscht.
Dornschließen sind an diversen Materialien zu finden und erstrecken sich in alle Preisklasse. Häufig findet man Dornschließen bei Lederarmbändern oder Textilarmbändern.

 Noch Fragen? Hier geht es zum Uhren-Lexikon, auf welcher zusätzlich das Logo graviert ist, verschlossen.

					Einmal eingestellt zeigt der Funksignalemfang immer die richtige Zeit an in Europa, Nordamerika, Japan und weiten Teilen Kanadas, sowie in Mittelamerika und China.
					

					Die Zeiger und IndizesIndizes ist das deutsche Wort für das lateinische Index. Spricht man von Indizes, dann sind die Zahlen die die Zeit anzeigen (bei vielen Uhren z.B. arabische Zahlen: 3, 6, 9, 12, aber auch z.B. römische Zahlen: III, VI, IX, XII) oder stattdessen die Platzhalter dafür gemeint. Platzhalter können je nach Gestaltung der Uhr die Unterschiedlichsten Formen haben. Uhrenindexe werden oft nicht nur aufgemalt sondern auch aufgesetzt – bei exklusiven Uhren auch veredelt (mit z.B. 					Das BarometerEin Barometer dient der Bemessung des statischen-absoluten Luftdrucks. Somit ist es möglich, eine vorzeitige Wettertendenz zu erkennen. 
Einige Uhren verfügen über einen Barometer. Dieser zeichnet sich anhand eines speziellen Sensors aus, welcher den Luftdruck misst. Dieser Wert wird symbolisch auf dem Display angezeigt. 



 Noch Fragen? Hier geht es zum Uhren-Lexikon misst den Luftdruck (Messbereich: 260/1.100 hPa.) und zeigt diesen symbolisch auf dem Display an.
					

					Das ThermometerEin Thermometer ist ein Gerät zur Messung der Temperaturen.  Noch Fragen? Hier geht es zum Uhren-Lexikon misst die Umgebungstemperatur der Uhr und zeigt diese in Grad Celsius (-10°C /+60°C) an.
					

					Die Weltzeit Funktion zeigt die Uhrzeiten in bis zu 29 verschiedenen ZeitzonenEs gibt insgesamt 24 Zeitzonen, die je 15 Längengrade umfassen und beim Nullmeridian beginnen. Beim Übergang von einer zur folgenden Zeitzone verschiebt sich die Zeit um eine Stunde. Je nach Himmelsrichtung verschiebt sich die Zeit entweder eine Stunde nach hinten ( Westen) oder nach vorne (Osten).
Die wichtigsten internationalen Zeitsignale sind: DCF77 (Deutschland) in Mainflingen in Hessen, MSF (Großbritannien) in Anthorn, JJY (Japan), WWV (USA) in Fort Collins, WWVH (USA) auf Hawaii, BPC (China) in Shangqiu

 Noch Fragen? Hier geht es zum Uhren-Lexikon an.
					

					Die Stopp-Funktion misst die abgelaufene Zeit, die Zwischenzeiten und Endzeit mit einer Genauigkeit von Hundertstelsekunden. Die Messkapazität der Uhr beträgt bis zu 24 Stunden.
					

					Der Countdown-Timer hilft bei der Erinnerung an Ereignisse, indem er zum eingestellten Zeitpunkt einen Signalton abgibt.
					

					Die 5 einstellbaren Tagesalarme geben beim Erreichen einen Signalton ab.
					

					Die automatische Zeigerjustierung prüft die Grund­stellung der Zeiger stündlich und korrigiert sie.
					

					Die Tastentöne können wahlweise ein- oder ausgeschaltet werden.
					

					Einmal eingestellt zeigt der automatische Kalender immer das richtige Datum an.
					

					Die Anzeige der Uhr ist wahlweise im 12- oder 24-Stunden-Format einstellbar.
					

					Die Batterie-Kontrollanzeige verhindern ein leerlaufen der Uhr.
					

					Ein besonders hartes und kratzfestes SaphirglasSaphirglas (Al2O3) ist von den üblichen Uhrengläsern das härteste. Lediglich der Diamant und einige Karbide weisen eine größere Härte auf und können Kratzer auf einem Saphirglas verursachen. Da Saphirglas relativ stark spiegelt, wird es häufig mit einer Beschichtung versehen (sog. 'Antireflex-Saphir'), die dann leider nicht dieselbe Widerstandsfähigkeit aufweist. Noch Fragen? Hier geht es zum Uhren-Lexikon schützt die UHr vor äußeren Einflüssen.
					

					Das Band ist aus Resin gefertigt und somit besonders langlebig und strapazierfähig.
					

					Verschlossen wird das Resinband mit einer DornschließeEine Dornschließe beschreibt die Verschlussart einer Uhr.  In dem längeren Armbandteil werden löcher gestanzt. Auf der anderen Seite befindet sich die Dornschließe, welche aus einem Dorn und einem Metallbügel in U-Form, diese verhindert, dass der Dorn aus dem Loch rutscht.
Dornschließen sind an diversen Materialien zu finden und erstrecken sich in alle Preisklasse. Häufig findet man Dornschließen bei Lederarmbändern oder Textilarmbändern.

Essential equipment for the lovers of the altitude, the Suunto Core is the professional pride of wristop computer ABC.

Look to the sky and we are the stars, but your Suunto Core tells you that a storm is coming. And I would say even with the storm alarm-one of many clever features that help you make good decisions. Building on the success of the Suunto Vector, Suunto Core will give you all the information you need thanks to its accurate functions: altimeter, barometer, digital thermometer, weather trend indicator and digital compass.

The barometer operate in four different modes, including an automatic setting that detects glthe moves, or lack thereof, and so is able to revert to therefore altimeter and barometer. "
					Artikel-Nr.: 4225 ECW-M300EDB-1AER
					
					Modern-funktionale Herrenuhr aus dem Hause Casio
					

					Full-Auto-LED Light: Um die Hintergrundbeleuchtung der Uhr zu aktivieren, genügt eine leichte Drehung des Handgelenks. Das funktioniert, sobald die Helligkeit in der Umgebung nachlässt.
					

					Solarfunktion: Unabhängig und umweltfreundlich sorgen Solarzellen für die Energieversorgung der Uhr. Überschüssige Solarenergie wird in einem Akku gespeichert.
					

					Funksignalempfang (EU, USA, Japan, China): Ob in Europa, Nordamerika und Japan oder in weiten Teilen Kanadas, Mittelamerikas und Chinas - nachdem die Uhr auf die örtliche Zeitzone eingestellt ist, empfängt sie das entsprechende Funksignal und zeigt immer die exakte Zeit an. In vielen Ländern stellt sie außerdem ganz eigenständig die Sommer- und Winterzeit ein.
					

					Neo-Display: Die Zeiger und/oder das Index sind fluoreszierend beschichtet und leuchten in der Dunkelheit nach, , wenn die Uhr zuvor einer Lichtquelle ausgesetzt war.
					

					Weltzeit Funktion: Die Weltzeit Funktion zeigt die Uhrzeiten in bis zu 29 verschiedenen ZeitzonenEs gibt insgesamt 24 Zeitzonen, die je 15 Längengrade umfassen und beim Nullmeridian beginnen. Beim Übergang von einer zur folgenden Zeitzone verschiebt sich die Zeit um eine Stunde. Je nach Himmelsrichtung verschiebt sich die Zeit entweder eine Stunde nach hinten ( Westen) oder nach vorne (Osten).
Die wichtigsten internationalen Zeitsignale sind: DCF77 (Deutschland) in Mainflingen in Hessen, MSF (Großbritannien) in Anthorn, JJY (Japan), WWV (USA) in Fort Collins, WWVH (USA) auf Hawaii, BPC (China) in Shangqiu

 Noch Fragen? Hier geht es zum Uhren-Lexikon an.
					

					Stoppfunktion - 1/100 Sek. - 24 Std.: Für Sportler und alle, die es genau wissen wollen: Abgelaufene Zeit, Zwischenzeit und Endzeit werden mit einer Genauigkeit von Hundertstelsekunden gemessen. Die Messkapazität der Uhr reicht bis zu 24 Stunden.
					

					Timer - 1/1 Min. - 1 Std. (mit aut. Wiederholfunktion): Für alle, die es genau wissen wollen: Der Countdown-Timer hilft bei der Erinnerung an besondere oder wiederkehrende Ereignisse, indem er zum eingestellten Zeitpunkt ein akustisches Signal abgibt ? anschließend zählt er automatisch wieder von der voreingestellten Zeit zurück. Die Zeit kann im Minuten Takt und bis zu 1 Stunde im Voraus eingestellt werden. Diese Funktion ist besonders praktisch für die tägliche Einnahme von Medikamenten oder Intervalltraining.
					

					5 Tagesalarme: An täglich wiederkehrende Ereignisse erinnert der Tagesalarm, bei dem ein akustisches Signal zum eingestellten Zeitpunkt ertönt. Zusätzlich macht ein abstellbarer Alarm auf den Ablauf jeder vollen Stunde aufmerksam. Dieses Modell verfügt über fünf unabhängige Alarme – besonders praktisch zur täglichen Einnahme von Medikamenten oder zum Einhalten regelmäßiger Termine.
					

					Schlummerfunktion: Nachdem Sie das Alarmsignal stoppen, ertönt es nach einigen Minuten automatisch wieder.
					

					Automatischer Kalender: Einmal eingestellt zeigt der automatische Kalender immer das richtige Datum an.
					

					12-/24-Stunden-Format: Die Zeitanzeige ist wahlweise einstellbar auf 12- oder 24-Stunden-Format. Im 12-Stunden-Modus steht ein p in der Anzeige für die zweite Tageshälfte, also 12 Uhr mittags bis 23.59 Uhr.
					

					Mineralglas: Das harte, kratzfeste Mineralglas schützt die Uhr vor unschönen Beschädigungen.
					

					Massives Edelstahlarmband: Hart, haltbar und elegant: Das massive Edelstahlarmband ist der hochwertige Klassiker für Uhren.
					

					Sicherheitsverschluss: Darauf ist Verlass: Das Armband dieser Uhr ist mit einem besonders sicheren Verschluss versehen, der ein versehentliches Öffnen verhindert.
					

					Ladekontrollanzeige: Mit dieser Kontrollanzeige hat man die Batterieladung der Uhr jederzeit im Blick.
					

					WasserdichtigkeitsDie Angaben über die  Wasserdichtigkeit von Uhren führen immer wieder zu Missverständnissen, da die  angegebenen Meterangaben meist wenig Aussagekraft haben. Im Folgenden nun ein  paar Richtlinien, die den richtigen Umgang mit ihrer Uhr und Wasser erleichtern  sollen:
Es kann auch vorkommen, dass die Angabe der Wasserdichtigkeit in Bar statt Metern vorliegt. Dies ist  dann folgendermaßen zu verstehen:
3 bar = 30 m / 5 bar = 50 m  / 10 bar = 100 m / 20 bar = 200 m 	 Noch Fragen? Hier geht es zum Uhren-Lexikon-Klassifizierung (10 Bar): Perfekt zum Schwimmen und Schnorcheln: Die Uhr ist wasserdicht bis 10 Bar / 100 Meter. title: " Junghans Men's Meister Driver Chronoscope Automatic Chronograph Watch"@en "Men's Watch (027/3684.00) - WATCH SHOP.com™"@en
description:
"Inspired by the friendship between Erhard Junghans, Wilhelm Maybach and Gottlieb Daimler, and the elegance of the cars of the 1930's, drove the creation of the Meister Driver collection.

The dials are designed with the same passion and integrity of design and detailing as the Maybach DS 8 Zeppelin, an expression of pure elegance and luxury. The watch is inspired by this automobile, down to the layout and detail of the numerals, as well as the colour combination of anthracite, cream and light grey, popular for the bodywork of the cars. The dial is designed to evoke the style of the speedometers and dashboard clocks of these vehicles, with large numerals and large hands for optimal readability. The strap is soft, supple padded leather, in a similar colour to the interior of the Maybach, and features an automatic movement, with chronograph."@en

                            The Cartier Tank, inspired by an actual tank, has been a design milestone since its inception in the early 20th century. Unlike the modified pocket watches being made by other manufacturers, the Tank used a new case design that actually incorporated the lugs into its shape, rather than adding them as an afterthought. Other iconic design elements include the blued sword hands, Roman numerals, elegant square dial and octagonal crown complete with sapphire cabochon. The Française collection adds a somewhat sportier, more modern feel to an already superb timepiece, making it bolder and more versatile, in large part thanks to its chain-link bracelet.
                            
                        "

title: "Rolex GMT Master II 116710 LN" LN Watch | Watchfinder & Co."
description:
"This Rolex has undergone a thorough inspection of water resistance, accuracy, functionality and condition to determine the level of reconditioning required to meet our strict standards. It has also been referenced against technical documents and manufacturer records where available to ensure authenticity and a clean history.", "
                            The GMT Master was first commissioned in the 1950s by pioneering airline Pan Am, and was designed for aviation. An increase in flight distances created demand for a watch that was able to tell the time in two different parts of the world simultaneously, so Rolex built it with an additional hand that could be set to a second time zone. By the 1980s, the watch had developed into the GMT Master II and was already a favourite among collectors. This model represents a significant upgrade for the watch, boasting an aerospace-grade “superalloy” steel case and cerachrom inserts in the bezel. The LN moniker stands for Lunette Noir—signifying that it uses an all-black bezel.
                            
                        "

title: "Max Bill Damenuhr"@de 00 €"@de "Junghans Max Damenuhr 047/4658.00 nur 495
description:
"
					Artikel-Nr.: 3522 047/4658.00
					
					Elegant-moderne Damenuhr der Marke Junghans.
					

					Das Gehäuse ist aus hochwertigem Edelstahl gefertigt und hat eine polierte Oberfläche.
					

					Auf dem roséfarbenen Zifferblatt befindet sich ein Junghans Schriftzug.
					

					Die Zeiger sind aus Edelstahl gefertigt und mit einer umweltfreundlichen Leuchtmasse beschichtet.
					

					Auf der 3-Uhr Position befindet sich eine Datumsanzeige.
					

					Der Zifferblattrand ist mit einer vollständigen MinuterieAuf dem Zifferblatt umlaufende Einteilung der Minuten, oft zwischen zwei Kreise eingefaßt (‘Eisenbahnminuterie = sieht aus wie Eisenbahnschienen) und teilweise mit ‘5’-Minutenzahlen versehen. Noch Fragen? Hier geht es zum Uhren-Lexikon versehen.
					

					Ein gewölbtes Plexi-Hartglas mit SICRALAN Beschichtung schützt die Uhr vor äußeren Einflüssen.
					

					Das Gehäuse hat einen Durchmesser von ca. 32.7 mm, die Höhe beträgt ca. 6,9 mm.
					

					Die Uhr wird durch ein präzises Quarzwerk KaliberDas Kaliber beschreibt die Form und die Größe eines Uhrwerks. Die Kalibernummer steht für den Werkstyp einer Uhr. ETA beispielsweise ist einer der größten Schweizer Anbieter mechanischer Werke. Anhand der Nummer kann ein Uhrenmacher im Bedarfsfall die passenden Ersatzteile für einen bestimmte Uhr bestimmen. Noch Fragen? Hier geht es zum Uhren-Lexikon J643.29 angetrieben.
					

					Das Band ist aus hochwertigem Kalbsleder gefertigt und verspricht einen hohen Tragekomfort.
					

					Das Band wird mit einer DornschließeEine Dornschließe beschreibt die Verschlussart einer Uhr.  In dem längeren Armbandteil werden löcher gestanzt. Auf der anderen Seite befindet sich die Dornschließe, welche aus einem Dorn und einem Metallbügel in U-Form, diese verhindert, dass der Dorn aus dem Loch rutscht.
Dornschließen sind an diversen Materialien zu finden und erstrecken sich in alle Preisklasse. Häufig findet man Dornschließen bei Lederarmbändern oder Textilarmbändern.

 Noch Fragen? Hier geht es zum Uhren-Lexikon aus Edelstahl verschlossen.
					

					100 Tage Niedrigpreisgarantie, bei uhrzeit.org kaufen Sie ohne Preisrisiko!
					

					Für unsere Waren bestehen die gesetzlichen Gewährleistungsrechte
						
				"@de

description:
"
                            The Cartier Tank, inspired by an actual tank, has been a design milestone since its inception in the early 20th century. Unlike the modified pocket watches being made by other manufacturers, the Tank used a new case design that actually incorporated the lugs into its shape, rather than adding them as an afterthought. Other iconic design elements include the blued sword hands, Roman numerals, elegant square dial and octagonal crown complete with sapphire cabochon. The Française collection adds a somewhat sportier, more modern feel to an already superb timepiece, making it bolder and more versatile, in large part thanks to its chain-link bracelet—which looks even better in this ravishing all-gold model.

title: "SUUNTO CORE REGULAR BLACK"@en BLACK - WATCH Suunto colour Black SS014809000 Athletic footwear apparel and sports equipment"@en
description:
"

Wristop computer watch for outdoor Suunto Core Regular Black model. A watch with altimeter, barometer and compass, in a durable composite case, with stainless steel frame and details.

Essential equipment for the lovers of the altitude, the Suunto Core is the professional pride of wristop computer ABC.

Look to the sky and we are the stars, but your Suunto Core tells you that a storm is coming. And I would say even with the storm alarm-one of many clever features that help you make good decisions. Building on the success of the Suunto Vector, Suunto Core will give you all the information you need thanks to its accurate functions: altimeter, barometer, digital thermometer, weather trend indicator and digital compass.

The barometer operate in four different modes, including an automatic setting that detects glthe moves, or lack thereof, and so is able to revert to therefore altimeter and barometer. The compass has a rotating bezel for traditional use and even a feature that lets you find, block and follow a bearing. Daily functions include dual time, date, alarm, Chronograph and sport time of sunrise and sunset.

The Suunto Core was chosen as great altimeter watch German Alpin magazine as a result of tests carried out in May 2009.

Technical characteristics

-Altimeter: altitude difference measurement/start from 0, logbook, automatic mode
-Barometer: Storm alarm, weather trend indicator, weather graph
-Compass: rotating bezel, digital bearing, easy calibration
-Depth: maximum depth 10 metres/30 feet
-Clock: Sunrise and tramonto, dual time, Stopwatch
-Other: button lock, 4 language Menu

title: "Rolex Milgauss 116400 GV" GV Watch | Watchfinder & Co."
description:
"This Rolex has undergone a thorough inspection of water resistance, accuracy, functionality and condition to determine the level of reconditioning required to meet our strict standards. It has also been referenced against technical documents and manufacturer records where available to ensure authenticity and a clean history.", "
                            Like many of its iconic watch families, Rolex's Milgauss was created in 1956 with a specific market in mind: scientists, power station workers and anyone else exposed to high magnetic fields. It was designed to be able to resist fields up to 1,000 gauss (hence the name—“mille” is Latin for thousand). The watch built a solid reputation with only two models until 1988, and was happily revived two decades later in a modern re-edition that remains faithful to the original purpose and aesthetics—including the beloved lightning bolt hand. This gorgeous GV version (Glace Verte) has a green-tinted dial crystal, and uses a Parachrom-Blu hairspring for even better magnetic and shock resistance.
                            
                        "

description:
"
                            The Seamaster is one of the most iconic diving watches of all time. Following on from Omega's Marine in 1932, the world's first commercially available diving watch, the legend of the Seamaster officially debuted in 1948. By the time of 1957's 300M, it was among the most dependable and professionally sought dive watches from any brand, and it soon pioneered some of the sporty must-have features we associate with such watches, including unidirectional bezels, phosphorescent hands and the helium escape valve. This excellent example takes the familiar technical specs and design cues from the early Seamasters and updates them with modern aesthetics.
